# ZenZone Product Backlog
SDG Goal: SDG 4 – Quality Education

This product backlog lists the main features and user stories for the ZenZone Study Buddy App.

---

1) Home Screen

- You can search for study buddies by subject here.

- There are buttons at the top:

      * Favorites - Save your favorite study buddies for easy access.

      * Dark mode - Switch to mode for easier reading.

      * Notifications - See who wants to study with you and respond.

      * Profile - Go to your profile page.


2) Timer

- Use the timer to help you study. You can choose Pomodoro or count-up timers.

- Start, pause or change your timer settings as needed.

- You can even. Chat with study buddies who are studying now.


3) Nudges

- See the recent nudge you got.

- You can quickly start a chat. Send a nudge back.

- Check your history if you need to.


4) Check-In

- See what you need to study today and track your progress.

- Click on tasks to check in and earn points.


5) Achievements

- Track how long you've been studying your badges and your goals.

- See quotes to keep you going.

- Check your streaks and total hours studied this week.


6) Available Study Buddies

- Look for study buddies who're available now.

- Filter by subject or time to find the match.


7) Messages

- Chat with your study group. Start a new group.


8) Calendar

- See your study sessions with buddies.

- Leave reviews for sessions and link to the buddy’s profile.


9) Profile

- See information, about your study buddies like what subjects they study and when they're available.

- Write reviews and rate study buddies.

- Buttons:

      * Send a study request. Choose a subject. Write a message.

      * Schedule a session. Add it to your calendar.

      * Send a nudge. Quick or custom.


10) My Profile

- Change your info and preferences here.

- See your connections, chats and study hours.

- You can log here too.



